{
  "texts": [
    "(2) Min-Max Normalization: Within each gesture, the 100 frames undergo a min-max normalization step.",
    "This normalization ensures that the values of the chirps and samples within each frame are scaled between zero and one.",
    "(3) Gesture Labeling: The index of the F Gesture obtained from the gesture frame detection process for the current gesture is retrieved.",
    "Subsequently, windowing is applied to label eight frames out of the 100 frames as gesture frames, as described in the earlier discussion.",
    "The remaining 92 frames are labeled with the Background class label."
  ]
}